SIX illegal firearms, including shotguns, 303 rifles and handguns were found hidden in a rondavel in Ndwedwe, north of KZN.Live rounds of ammunition were also found in the house. A 60-year-old man who was found in the house was arrested after he failed to give a satisfactory explanation to the police.The joint operation by various police units was conducted at Ndwedwe on Wednesday after cops received a tip-off about illegal firearms and ammunition. KZN police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala said the cops followed up the information which led them to a house in the Gonothini area ofNdwedwe. &ldquo;On arrival, members searched a homestead which was identified to them as the place where firearms were kept. A total of six unlicensed firearms, including handguns, shotguns and 303 rifles were found in a rondavel.&rdquo; She said all these recovered firearms will be sent for ballistic tests to establish if they had been used in any crimes. KZN provincial commissioner, Major-General Bheki Langa, praised the members for their excellent work that led to the recovery of such firearms. &ldquo;By recovering such firearms, we have saved many people that could have been attacked by the criminals using these firearms. &ldquo;I also thank members of the community who reported these firearms to the police. Your continuous support in fighting crime is highly appreciated,&rdquo; he said.